<li id="cite_note-4"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-4">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">"witch" here translates the Hebrew <span lang="he" xml:lang="he">מכשפה</span>, and is rendered <span lang="grc" xml:lang="grc">φαρμακός</span> in the <a href="/wiki/Septuagint" title="Septuagint">Septuagint</a>.</span></li>
<li id="cite_note-5"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-5">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">"those that have familiar spirits": Hebrew <span lang="he" xml:lang="he">אוב</span>, or <span lang="grc" xml:lang="grc">ἐγγαστρίμυθος</span> "ventriloquist, soothsayer" in the Septuagint; "wizards": Hebrew <span lang="he" xml:lang="he">ידעני</span> or <span lang="grc" xml:lang="grc">γνώστης</span> "diviner" in the Septuagint.</span></li>
